However, if no pet is given, we assume nothing about her number of pets: she still might have had pets or not. Empirically, the PCA has been found to be frequently satisfied in KBs (see Section (ref) - paragraph ``Weak Signals''). Still, the PCA is a generic assumption, and does not allow the specification of individual regions of completeness/incompleteness.